300 2766 1741 (The various iterator categories as currently defined are distinct.  However, a random access iterator is a) 1741 SB
300 2816 1760 (bidirectional iterator, and a bidirectional iterator is a forward iterator.  The iterator tags and base classes) 1760 SB
300 2866 1707 (for these iterators could be related through inheritance.  This could make the definition of algorithms) 1707 SB
300 2916 1796 (easier.  For example, an algorithm that tested for an iterator category of forward could be passed a random) 1796 SB
